  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sustainable, Healthful Agriculture in Agrarian Reform Areas of Brasil</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will be implemented in the state of Rio Grande do Sul, in the Agrarian Reform settlements of the Porto Alegre Region. Production for large scale export and the use of agrochemicals for agricultural production have generated serious social and environmental consequences, obliging thousands of poor small farmer families to leave the countryside and settle in the shanty towns found in and around big cities. This project will allow many of these families to remain in the countryside, aiming not only to generate income and promote care of the land by consolidating agroecological rice growing, but also to strengthen sustainable food systems through collective action. A total of 561 original families will benefit, while another 2,420 will benefit from passing on the gift. Agroecological training, agricultural equipment, seeds and plants will be provided to improve existing production systems.</narrative>
  </description>
